# e-- fork provenance

Upstream: https://github.com/frmoded/e--
Base pin: da8c3b34d2493180da8df65b127a3841f9a4e609
License: Apache-2.0. The upstream `LICENSE` is retained verbatim in this directory.

## Fork pin

The vendored fork identity (the "fork pin") is the base pin plus the ordered `patches/` set plus the SHA-256 tree manifest `MANIFEST.sha256`.

Patches MUST be git-format patches named `NNNN-<slug>.patch`, applied in lexical order on top of the base pin. Each patch MUST be minimal and independently re-applicable. The ordered patch set is:

- `0001-lazy-package-transpile-import.patch` — defer the quarantined legacy transpiler import with PEP 562 while preserving the public API.
- `0002-add-strict-compilation-entrypoint.patch` — add the stdlib-only validated compiler entry point.
- `0003-add-strict-tcb-language-extensions.patch` — add top-level imports, dotted references and call targets, requirements, and explicit exits.

Compatibility note: `Use`, `Require that`, and `Exit with` become statement keywords at head position. A grep of upstream tests and examples found zero collisions (exit 1; verified 2026-07-18).

The vendored upstream file tree is byte-identical to the base pin plus this ordered patch set.

Any TCB change MUST pass the "bump fork pin" gate: update the patch set, regenerate `MANIFEST.sha256`, and update `docs/provenance.md`.

## Python TCB file allowlist

CORE — strict compilation path:

- `src/e_minus_minus/lexer.py` — lexical analysis.
- `src/e_minus_minus/parser.py` — parsing into the compiler AST.
- `src/e_minus_minus/emitter.py` — Python emission.
- `src/e_minus_minus/ast_nodes.py` — compiler AST definitions.
- `src/e_minus_minus/errors.py` — compiler error definitions.
- `src/e_minus_minus/strict.py` — strict compilation entry point, added in M1.2.

QUARANTINED — retained for upstream fidelity; the strict path MUST NEVER load these files:

- `src/e_minus_minus/transpiler.py` — legacy high-level transpilation path.
- `src/e_minus_minus/normalizer.py` — normalization path.
- `src/e_minus_minus/resolver.py` — slot-resolution path.
- `src/e_minus_minus/cli.py` — legacy CLI path.

`src/e_minus_minus/__init__.py` is retained for upstream fidelity; `0001-lazy-package-transpile-import.patch` supplies its M1.2 PEP 562 lazy import.

Quarantine is a deny-list, not an "imports only" rule: the strict path MUST NOT import or otherwise load `transpiler`, `normalizer`, `resolver`, `cli`, or `anthropic`. Standard-library imports and the CORE modules, including `ast_nodes` and `errors`, are legal.

Upstream `tests/` is vendored third-party test code, not first-party Python.

## Fidelity checks

Run from the repository root. Clone upstream into scratch (or reuse a local clone), check out the base pin, archive it into a clean scratch tree, apply every local patch in lexical order, hash both comparable trees, and compare them:

```sh
set -eu
ROOT=$PWD
PIN=da8c3b34d2493180da8df65b127a3841f9a4e609
UPSTREAM="$ROOT/.scratch/e---upstream"
WORK="$ROOT/.scratch/e---fidelity"

# Omit clone when reusing an existing local clone.
git clone https://github.com/frmoded/e-- "$UPSTREAM"
git -C "$UPSTREAM" checkout --detach "$PIN"
rm -rf "$WORK"
mkdir -p "$WORK"
git -C "$UPSTREAM" archive "$PIN" | tar -x -C "$WORK"

for patch in "$ROOT"/vendor/e--/patches/*.patch; do
    [ -e "$patch" ] || break
    (cd "$WORK" && git apply "$patch")
done

(
    cd "$WORK"
    find . -type f -print0 | LC_ALL=C sort -z | xargs -0 sha256sum
) > "$ROOT/.scratch/e---base.sha256"
(
    cd "$ROOT/vendor/e--"
    find . -type f \
        ! -path './PROVENANCE' \
        ! -path './MANIFEST.sha256' \
        ! -path './patches/*' \
        -print0 | LC_ALL=C sort -z | xargs -0 sha256sum
) > "$ROOT/.scratch/e---vendor.sha256"
diff -u "$ROOT/.scratch/e---base.sha256" "$ROOT/.scratch/e---vendor.sha256"
```

With patches present, the vendor tree MUST equal the base pin plus those patches applied in lexical order. The in-tree integrity check is:

```sh
cd vendor/e-- && sha256sum -c MANIFEST.sha256
```
